Goal of the analysis¶

  1. Use text mining to do sentiment analysis
  2. Use different models to compare the analysis results (Valder, Naive Bayes)
  3. Creat Tokenization and DTM
  4. Manupalate dataset with Word Cloud, Corcordance, colocation of bigram/trigram

Dataset source¶

This dataset if from Kaggle

Content

This dataset contains the following attributes:

Total Records: 568454 Total Columns: 10 Domain Name: amazon.com  File Extension: CSV

Available Fields: Id, ProductId, UserId, ProfileName, HelpfulnessNumerator, HelpfulnessDenomenator, Score, Time, Summary, Text

# Accuracy - sia v.s. existing scores
sia_score_mapping = reviews.groupby([pd.cut(reviews.sia,buckets),'Score']).count()   # count score dist# in ranges of sia

sia_score_mapping.drop(columns='sia',inplace=True)  # The following codes to create a dataframe for plotting
sia_score_mapping = sia_score_mapping.reset_index()
sia_score_number = list(sia_score_mapping['Id'])    # Here 'Id' represents # of ecah Score in sia ranges
sia_score_number_cut = [sia_score_number[i:i+5] for i in range(0,len(sia_score_number),5)]  # divide the list
df = pd.DataFrame(sia_score_number_cut, index=sia_score_mapping.sia.unique(),columns=sia_score_mapping.Score.unique())
print(df)
df.plot(kind="bar",figsize=(15, 6))
plt.title('Actual scores distribution on sia values')
plt.xlabel('Vader sia values')
plt.ylabel('Number of Actual Scores')

df1 = df.reset_index(drop=True)
df1.index = [1,2,3,4,5]
total_correct = 0
for i in df1.index:
    total_correct += df1.loc[i,i]         # the # of sia that align with scores
vader_accuracy_rate = total_correct/df.sum().sum()*100
print('\nThe overall accuracy of Vader sentiment analysis is {}%'.format(vader_accuracy_rate))

# Concordance Manupulation ('flavor', 'return')

con_word = 'flavor'
print('------The word [{}] concordance result:--------'.format(con_word))
k = 0
for i in reviews_1.index: 
    if k == 10:                             # Only display 10 records
        break
    #print(reviews_1.loc[i,'Text'])
    if con_word in reviews_1.loc[i,'Text']:
        text = Text(reviews_1.loc[i,'Text'])
        text.concordance(con_word)
        k+=1

print('\n\n')

# Accuracy - sia v.s. existing scores
sia_score_mapping = reviews.groupby([pd.cut(reviews.sia,buckets),'Score']).count()   # count score dist# in ranges of sia

sia_score_mapping.drop(columns='sia',inplace=True)  # The following codes to create a dataframe for plotting
sia_score_mapping = sia_score_mapping.reset_index()

sia_score_number = list(sia_score_mapping['Id'])    # Here 'Id' represents # of ecah Score in sia ranges
sia_score_number_cut = [sia_score_number[i:i+5] for i in range(0,len(sia_score_number),5)]  # divide the list
df = pd.DataFrame(sia_score_number_cut, index=sia_score_mapping.sia.unique(),columns=sia_score_mapping.Score.unique())

df1 = df.reset_index(drop=True)
df1.index = [0, 1]
total_correct = 0

# dropping the column 3
df1.drop(columns=3, inplace=True)

# merging 1, 2 as 0 and 4, 5 as 1
df1[0] = df1[1]+df1[2]
df1.drop(columns=[1, 2], inplace=True)
df1[1] = df1[4]+df1[5]
df1.drop(columns=[4, 5], inplace=True)
print(df1)

df1.plot(kind="bar",figsize=(15, 6))
plt.title('Actual scores distribution on sia values')
plt.xlabel('Vader sia values')
plt.ylabel('Number of Actual Scores')

for i in df1.index:
    total_correct += df1.loc[i,i]         # the # of sia that align with scores
vader_accuracy_rate = total_correct/df.sum().sum()*100
print('\nThe overall accuracy of Vader sentiment analysis is {}%'.format(vader_accuracy_rate))
